    "heading:895": {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "heading:895",
      "level": 2,
      "content": "Calculation of atomic positional probability",
      "nodes": []
    },
    "text:896": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text:896",
      "content": "All atoms comprising the ensemble are assigned a probability (Pi) based on the positional likelihood of atom i in a given model relative to the complete ensemble of models. Fcalc electron-density maps are calculated for each model in the ensemble and 〈Fcalc〉 electron-density map is calculated for the complete ensemble as (10). Pi is calculated as (12)."
    },
    "formula:eqn12": {
      "type": "formula",
      "id": "formula:eqn12",
      "label": "(12)",
      "content": "<mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>ρ</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mo>〈</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant=bold-italic>F</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant=italic>calc</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo>〉</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>ρ</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant=bold-italic>F</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant=italic>calc</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow>"
    },
    "text:915": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text:915",
      "content": "Calculating from an electron-density function allows for non-Gaussian distributions unlike RMSF, which is calculated from mean atomic position. These probabilities aid the visual inspection of the ensemble models and allow the observer to control the level of detail displayed (Figure 14)."
    },
